message.content: So he put up for the night at The Admiral's Head, that famous Portsmouth hostelry, second only in historic interest to The George, unhappily destroyed by German bombs during the last war. Having deposited his luggage and unpacked his overnight-bag he went in search of a drink. The lower bar was empty, save for the lady known by all habitués as 'Seaweed' and a youngish, sharp-eyed man who was sloshing moodily into a gin and tonic.
